write_utf8(c('# Claims Audit','',
'This audit reviewed causal and prescriptive language in public narrative files. The paper and README were revised to use observational language where no causal identification exists.','','| File/section | Original or risky wording | Problem | Correction | Status |','|---|---|---|---|---|','| `paper/main.qmd`, research question | "helps explain divergent structural transformation" | Could be read as causal explanation. | Reframed as "help characterize divergent structural transformation patterns" and descriptive analysis. | Corrected |','| `paper/main.qmd`, econometric evidence | "raising ECI mechanically raises growth" | Explicit causal claim would be unsupported. | Text now states this is not proven and models are observational associations. | Corrected |','| `paper/policy_brief.qmd`, risks | "Policy should balance" | Could sound prescriptive without feasibility evidence. | Rewritten as policy use and screening guidance, with sector-study caveat. | Corrected |','| `README.md`, key findings | Product opportunity categories | Could be read as investment advice. | README now states rankings are screening tools, not prescriptions. | Corrected |','| `dashboard/app.R`, Opportunity Lab | Ranked product table | User may interpret ordering as recommendation. | Visible note added: rankings are screening tools, not investment prescriptions. | Corrected |','','Residual risk: terms such as "implication" and "policy" remain where they describe interpretation, not identified causal effects.'), p('docs/CLAIMS_AUDIT.md'))
write_utf8(c('# Table Audit','',
'Phase 3 reviewed tables used directly or indirectly by the paper. Main text tables are limited to conceptual definitions and key result summaries; detailed validation and model tables remain in outputs or appendix references.','','| Table | Location | Use | Audit result |','|---|---|---|---|','| Conceptual definitions | `paper/tables/conceptual_definitions.csv` and `.md` | Main conceptual clarity | PASS: definitions, role and caveats included. |','| Bolivia 2023 validation | `outputs/tables/csv/bolivia_2023_indicator_validation.csv` | Numerical consistency | PASS: values match reported ECI, diversity, HHI and primary share. |','| Econometric model summary | `outputs/tables/csv/econometric_model_summary.csv` | Model discussion | PASS: includes estimates, standard errors, p-values, N, R2 and within R2. Text explains fixed effects and clustered SE. |','| Opportunity table | `outputs/tables/csv/bolivia_opportunities_revised.csv` | Opportunity section and dashboard | PASS: includes absolute and relative categories, scores and eligibility. Notes warn against prescriptions. |','| Figure audit | `outputs/tables/csv/figure_audit.csv` | Figure readiness | PASS: 11/11 figure records pass existence and size checks. |','','Recommendation: keep detailed rankings and model outputs outside the main text and cite them as reproducible outputs.'), p('docs/TABLE_AUDIT.md'))
